Sentencas: Haynes 230 alloy was exposed to reducing and oxidizing environments at 750degreesC for 1000 h, simulating the conditions in a reduced temperature solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC).
Titulo: Oxidation of Haynes 230 alloy in reduced temperature solid oxide fuel cell environments

Sentencas: The oxidized specimens were characterized in terms of the oxide morphology, composition and crystal structure.
Titulo: Oxidation of Haynes 230 alloy in reduced temperature solid oxide fuel cell environments

Sentencas: The oxide scale in each environment was identified as Cr2O3 with the existence of Cr2MnO4.
Titulo: Oxidation of Haynes 230 alloy in reduced temperature solid oxide fuel cell environments

Sentencas: Ni remained metallic in the reducing atmosphere, and NiO was detected in the sample exposed to air.
Titulo: Oxidation of Haynes 230 alloy in reduced temperature solid oxide fuel cell environments

Sentencas: The oxide scale is around 1 mum thick after 1000 h of oxidation in both situations.
Titulo: Oxidation of Haynes 230 alloy in reduced temperature solid oxide fuel cell environments

Sentencas: The area specific resistance (ASR) contributed by the oxide scale is expected less than 0.1 Omega cm(2) after 40,000 h of exposure when a parabolic oxide growth rate is assumed, demonstrating the suitability of the interconnect application of this alloy in the reduced temperature SOFCs.
Titulo: Oxidation of Haynes 230 alloy in reduced temperature solid oxide fuel cell environments
